1
00:00:14,805 --> 00:00:20,243
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:21,078 --> 00:00:28,985
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:29,052 --> 00:00:34,422
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,491 --> 00:00:38,552
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,796 --> 00:00:44,699
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:45,435 --> 00:00:52,341
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,744 --> 00:00:57,236
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:57,314 --> 00:01:04,277
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:04,354 --> 00:01:11,419
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,495 --> 00:01:18,162
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,569 --> 00:01:28,137
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:01:49,210 --> 00:01:51,474
It's close.

13
00:02:02,156 --> 00:02:03,885
That's strange.

14
00:02:04,559 --> 00:02:07,289
There hasn't been even
one trap set for a while...

15
00:02:08,296 --> 00:02:10,321
Shikamaru, what do you think?

16
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:14,791
We're being underestimated.

17
00:02:15,436 --> 00:02:20,499
Those guys think the only one
following them is that big guy.

18
00:02:21,209 --> 00:02:24,007
They don't need to set
a trap on their man.

19
00:02:24,078 --> 00:02:27,206
How dare they underestimate us!

20
00:02:27,949 --> 00:02:29,883
It seems you're right.

21
00:02:30,752 --> 00:02:33,687
We are being
completely underestimated.

22
00:02:34,889 --> 00:02:37,983
However, this is our chance.

23
00:02:41,396 --> 00:02:45,025
Yeah... We'll take them by surprise.

24
00:02:48,770 --> 00:02:54,208
<i>Your Opponent is Me!</i>

25
00:03:07,822 --> 00:03:09,790
That Jirobo is late.

26
00:03:10,558 --> 00:03:13,026
No, he's already here.

27
00:03:18,766 --> 00:03:21,963
Aw, c'mon, what took you so long?

28
00:03:22,770 --> 00:03:24,067
Sorry.

29
00:03:24,939 --> 00:03:28,306
It took time to eat the scums' Chakra.

30
00:03:30,411 --> 00:03:33,778
Hey fatso, don't you dare drag!

31
00:03:34,449 --> 00:03:36,747
Hurry up and carry that coffin...

32
00:03:36,818 --> 00:03:40,845
That's your job, you vulgar swine.

33
00:03:41,255 --> 00:03:42,187
I know.

34
00:03:47,195 --> 00:03:51,222
What, Jirobo...
You're awfully easygoing today.

35
00:03:52,467 --> 00:03:53,559
What do you mean?

36
00:03:54,969 --> 00:03:58,735
I'm just saying I'm not handing you
the coffin.

37
00:03:58,906 --> 00:04:01,238
Because you're not Jirobo!

38
00:04:09,984 --> 00:04:11,781
This time let me do it.

39
00:04:12,053 --> 00:04:14,954
Sakon, Tayuya, you guys go ahead!

40
00:04:21,295 --> 00:04:25,595
Jirobo always corrects
Tayuya's choice of words.

41
00:04:29,537 --> 00:04:31,471
Heh, I see.

42
00:04:33,174 --> 00:04:34,937
<i>Ninja Art. Spider Web Net.</i>

43
00:04:44,852 --> 00:04:47,047
You!

44
00:04:53,161 --> 00:04:54,822
Ninja Art: Spiral Spider Web

45
00:05:00,368 --> 00:05:01,494
Naruto!

46
00:05:01,869 --> 00:05:03,860
<i>Now Kiba, Akamaru!</i>

47
00:05:04,138 --> 00:05:07,471
<i>He shouldn't be able to</i>
<i>move in mid air.</i>

48
00:05:09,110 --> 00:05:10,304
Fang Over Fang!

49
00:05:17,552 --> 00:05:18,780
I won't let you get away!

50
00:05:21,088 --> 00:05:23,079
That's my line.

51
00:05:23,891 --> 00:05:25,415
Look at your feet.

52
00:05:28,596 --> 00:05:29,688
You!

53
00:05:29,997 --> 00:05:32,966
It's too soon for you to think
you captured us with a thing like this!

54
00:05:35,770 --> 00:05:36,828
Shut up!

55
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:43,309
C'mon, what the hell is
that fatso doing, dammit!

56
00:05:43,878 --> 00:05:48,713
It was a mistake to leave
behind the weakest of us, after all.

57
00:06:01,495 --> 00:06:02,553
<i>Got it.</i>

58
00:06:11,806 --> 00:06:13,569
- Neji!
- What?!

59
00:06:14,976 --> 00:06:17,342
<i>Me, Naruto, Kiba and Neji...</i>

60
00:06:17,445 --> 00:06:19,913
<i>Even though we've followed the plan,</i>
<i>it's no good.</i>

61
00:06:36,097 --> 00:06:38,588
I'm going to cocoon you.

62
00:06:44,405 --> 00:06:45,667
Damn!

63
00:06:50,077 --> 00:06:52,136
Damn it! Damn it!

64
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:55,540
What's with this thread?! It won't cut.

65
00:07:00,955 --> 00:07:02,445
It's useless.

66
00:07:02,790 --> 00:07:06,021
My thread is so strong that
even if two elephants pulled away,

67
00:07:06,093 --> 00:07:07,993
it wouldn't break.

68
00:07:12,166 --> 00:07:14,464
Shadow Clone... Interesting.

69
00:07:26,814 --> 00:07:28,543
<i>The thread is sticking...</i>

70
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:31,741
<i>This stickiness is probably made</i>

71
00:07:31,819 --> 00:07:35,448
<i>by mixing Chakra with</i>
<i>his special body fluid.</i>

72
00:07:36,157 --> 00:07:39,957
<i>Moreover, this strength. Even after</i>
<i>it's been released from his hands...</i>

73
00:07:40,294 --> 00:07:43,661
<i>Chakra's continuously flowing</i>
<i>in the thread.</i>

74
00:07:45,299 --> 00:07:50,737
<i>It's impossible...</i>
<i>The level of the Jutsu is unrealistic.</i>

75
00:07:52,740 --> 00:07:55,709
<i>Calm down... Just calm down...</i>

76
00:07:57,278 --> 00:07:58,540
<i>my Chakra.</i>

77
00:08:14,695 --> 00:08:17,357
<i>Ninja Art.</i>
<i>Gum Style Spider Thread.</i>

78
00:08:18,232 --> 00:08:20,792
<i>It's a different color than</i>
<i>the thread from before.</i>

79
00:08:21,635 --> 00:08:22,761
<i>What's he gonna do?</i>

80
00:08:33,614 --> 00:08:35,809
<i>It's quickly solidifying, huh...</i>

81
00:08:38,552 --> 00:08:41,783
You are the first one,
so it's like a little entertainment.

82
00:08:42,089 --> 00:08:46,150
Now I'll play a game to see
which of you is the real one.

83
00:08:46,227 --> 00:08:47,694
What did you say?!

84
00:08:49,130 --> 00:08:52,293
First is... you at the end.

85
00:08:54,535 --> 00:08:55,866
Naruto!

86
00:08:58,739 --> 00:09:02,470
It was a clone, huh.
Well, this one next!

87
00:09:08,549 --> 00:09:10,380
What a lucky guy.

88
00:09:10,951 --> 00:09:15,183
Next, I'll do two at a time.
The odds are 2 to 1.

89
00:09:31,138 --> 00:09:36,166
This guy has a great luck,
but it's either one or the other now!

90
00:09:48,055 --> 00:09:50,717
Turns out he made it to the last.

91
00:09:51,425 --> 00:09:57,796
Well, it was fun as a game,
but now the game's over.

92
00:10:02,336 --> 00:10:02,961
Die!

93
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:08,437
The first one is done.

94
00:10:10,277 --> 00:10:10,902
What?!

95
00:10:25,392 --> 00:10:29,260
<i>I see, the real body made</i>
<i>its shadow clones get caught,</i>

96
00:10:29,330 --> 00:10:32,629
<i>and hid himself and</i>
<i>waited for a chance, huh.</i>

97
00:10:33,601 --> 00:10:37,799
<i>For a small fish like that to make</i>
<i>such a plan in those circumstances...</i>

98
00:10:38,339 --> 00:10:41,797
You're not too bad... but...

99
00:10:47,515 --> 00:10:49,449
You're at the end of the line. Die!

100
00:10:53,053 --> 00:10:53,951
What?!

101
00:10:54,588 --> 00:10:57,284
Naruto, your stall was helpful.

102
00:10:57,725 --> 00:10:58,453
Neji!

103
00:11:00,694 --> 00:11:04,027
You... How...?!

104
00:11:07,501 --> 00:11:10,129
Substance with Chakra base...

105
00:11:11,071 --> 00:11:13,096
It's meaningless in front
of Gentle Fist

106
00:11:13,174 --> 00:11:15,506
that destroys by pouring
Chakra through.

107
00:11:16,877 --> 00:11:18,367
<i>That guy's Jutsu...</i>

108
00:11:20,814 --> 00:11:23,942
<i>Evidently I'm the only one</i>
<i>who can fight it.</i>

109
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:27,150
Go!

110
00:11:28,989 --> 00:11:30,183
I'll take care of this.

111
00:11:50,678 --> 00:11:53,647
What's wrong? Hey, Akamaru.

112
00:11:54,982 --> 00:11:58,577
Apparently, this guy's stronger
than the fatso before.

113
00:11:59,787 --> 00:12:01,482
Quite a bit stronger.

114
00:12:08,062 --> 00:12:10,326
If we're not prepared for
"one person, one kill,"

115
00:12:10,397 --> 00:12:11,796
then it's not going to work out.

116
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:14,295
That's what you said earlier.

117
00:12:15,102 --> 00:12:18,230
Yeah, that's right.

118
00:12:19,573 --> 00:12:23,839
Plus, we won't be able to catch up
with Sasuke if we stall here.

119
00:12:24,144 --> 00:12:26,009
Choji hasn't come back either.

120
00:12:33,053 --> 00:12:34,884
The reason we're doing this

121
00:12:34,955 --> 00:12:37,321
is because of the mission
to bring back Sasuke.

122
00:12:38,559 --> 00:12:40,151
But that's not all.

123
00:12:41,028 --> 00:12:44,293
What we are after and trying
to protect is the bond

124
00:12:44,365 --> 00:12:47,027
of the Shinobi of
the Village Hidden in the Leaves.

125
00:12:49,169 --> 00:12:54,266
Do you remember Iruka's words
at the Third Hokage's funeral?

126
00:13:01,615 --> 00:13:09,522
Iruka Sensei, why do people risk
their lives for others?

127
00:13:13,227 --> 00:13:16,663
When someone dies,

128
00:13:18,132 --> 00:13:22,228
they depart with their past,
present and future.

129
00:13:23,103 --> 00:13:26,470
Many people die on missions
or at war.

130
00:13:27,041 --> 00:13:31,068
And their death is surprisingly
unceremonious... they simply die.

131
00:13:32,313 --> 00:13:34,110
Hayate was one of those people.

132
00:13:35,182 --> 00:13:38,913
Those who die have dreams
and goals, too...

133
00:13:39,987 --> 00:13:44,321
But everyone has things that
are equally important.

134
00:13:45,659 --> 00:13:50,289
Parents, siblings, friends, lovers,
the people of their village,

135
00:13:50,364 --> 00:13:52,332
the people important to you.

136
00:13:53,467 --> 00:13:56,300
The connection to the people
you trust and help mutually,

137
00:13:56,370 --> 00:14:00,773
the people important to you
from the day you were born.

138
00:14:02,242 --> 00:14:06,474
And the thread that
connects you and your people

139
00:14:06,547 --> 00:14:08,606
gets stronger through time.

140
00:14:10,250 --> 00:14:11,808
It's not a theory.

141
00:14:12,619 --> 00:14:16,248
That's what a person does
as the thread is established

142
00:14:16,890 --> 00:14:18,721
because they're important to you...

143
00:14:26,033 --> 00:14:30,367
Look, Sasuke is heading
towards Orochimaru.

144
00:14:30,971 --> 00:14:34,134
We can't let Orochimaru get
a hold of someone from our village.

145
00:14:35,776 --> 00:14:36,708
Absolutely not.

146
00:14:38,812 --> 00:14:40,074
And...

147
00:14:54,128 --> 00:14:55,186
Naruto...

148
00:14:57,498 --> 00:15:00,262
Your eyes are better than mine.

149
00:15:06,707 --> 00:15:07,833
Right now, Sasuke is...

150
00:15:11,678 --> 00:15:13,111
in the darkness.

151
00:15:23,524 --> 00:15:27,585
Hurry up and go!
I'll catch up with you all!

152
00:15:30,164 --> 00:15:30,926
Gotcha!

153
00:15:33,534 --> 00:15:35,502
Okay! Let's go!

154
00:15:36,470 --> 00:15:39,064
You along with Choji,
be sure to catch up!

155
00:15:40,741 --> 00:15:41,730
Yeah...

156
00:15:54,154 --> 00:15:57,317
<i>Neji, be absolutely sure to catch up!</i>

157
00:16:02,362 --> 00:16:04,592
Heh... think I'll let them get away?!

158
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:07,798
<i>Byakugan!</i>

159
00:16:15,042 --> 00:16:16,100
Here it comes!

160
00:16:28,155 --> 00:16:30,589
This guy's pretty good...

161
00:16:34,394 --> 00:16:35,486
Neji!

162
00:16:35,762 --> 00:16:37,024
That's Neji all right!

163
00:16:40,033 --> 00:16:43,366
<i>Not yet...</i>
<i>I won't let you escape that easily!</i>

164
00:16:46,807 --> 00:16:48,741
I won't let you go any further from here!

165
00:16:54,147 --> 00:16:55,341
It's useless.

166
00:16:59,353 --> 00:17:00,752
Well, that's fine.

167
00:17:01,321 --> 00:17:05,485
It seems you're the strongest
out of the lot.

168
00:17:08,362 --> 00:17:12,298
Aw man, now I wanna play...

169
00:17:12,966 --> 00:17:16,834
It's such a waste if
a game isn't played little by little.

170
00:17:39,493 --> 00:17:42,656
For starters,
I'll play and kill you in three minutes.

171
00:18:44,057 --> 00:18:45,319
I got you.

172
00:18:49,229 --> 00:18:56,067
You're pretty good at handling Chakra
and you've got sharp eyes.

173
00:18:56,937 --> 00:18:59,770
You release Chakra from
the Chakra points in your hands

174
00:18:59,840 --> 00:19:01,535
like a sharp needle.

175
00:19:01,942 --> 00:19:06,572
You see the thin part of the thread
with Chakra running through it, and attack.

176
00:19:10,717 --> 00:19:13,447
I see, I've heard from Lord Orochimaru...

177
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:16,045
This is what's called Gentle Fist, isn't it?

178
00:19:18,725 --> 00:19:21,785
But if you can't use
those annoying hands,

179
00:19:21,862 --> 00:19:24,228
they can't cut my threads either.

180
00:19:27,534 --> 00:19:32,062
Man, games. The instant you know
the rules of engagement,

181
00:19:32,139 --> 00:19:34,505
they're no longer interesting.

182
00:19:35,409 --> 00:19:39,675
It's only been a minute,
but I'm already tired of you.

183
00:19:56,530 --> 00:19:57,690
<i>Die!</i>

184
00:20:01,668 --> 00:20:03,863
<i>Ninja Art.</i>
<i>Gum Style Spider Thread</i>

185
00:20:20,587 --> 00:20:21,281
<i>What?!</i>

186
00:20:33,366 --> 00:20:35,027
<i>How did he...?!</i>

187
00:20:36,236 --> 00:20:38,727
I'll explain, specially to you.

188
00:20:39,673 --> 00:20:41,197
It's not just my hands

189
00:20:42,576 --> 00:20:46,376
I can release Chakra from
all of the Chakra points on my body.

190
00:20:48,081 --> 00:20:51,710
And it's game over.

191
00:20:56,957 --> 00:21:01,018
Gentle Fist: 8 trigrams 64 palms.

192
00:21:13,607 --> 00:21:20,706
<i>Once in a long while, once in a while</i>

193
00:21:20,847 --> 00:21:26,376
<i>The remnants of a person</i>
<i>broken by dreams</i>

194
00:21:26,553 --> 00:21:31,616
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

195
00:21:34,928 --> 00:21:41,925
<i>Clinging to the Divine,</i>
<i>clinging to Buddha</i>

196
00:21:42,002 --> 00:21:47,531
<i>The remnants of a person crying</i>

197
00:21:47,941 --> 00:21:51,502
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

198
00:21:53,180 --> 00:21:56,240
<i>Rendezvous with a happy dance circle</i>

199
00:21:56,316 --> 00:22:00,116
<i>This is my victory pose, round and around</i>
<i>(round around)</i>

200
00:22:00,453 --> 00:22:03,388
<i>Shake shake shake</i>
<i>Let's look</i>

201
00:22:03,456 --> 00:22:07,586
<i>With a bye bye rhythm that never ends</i>

202
00:22:16,770 --> 00:22:21,867
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

203
00:22:23,810 --> 00:22:27,075
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

204
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:30,677
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

205
00:22:30,951 --> 00:22:34,944
<i>Look like a mountain</i>

206
00:22:40,026 --> 00:22:41,857
The attack on his Chakra points
is ineffective.

207
00:22:41,928 --> 00:22:42,758
On top of that,

208
00:22:42,829 --> 00:22:46,356
he switched to a long distance attack
to avoid Gentle Fist.

209
00:22:46,733 --> 00:22:50,897
This guy blocks my every move
and he quickly reads my hands.

210
00:22:51,304 --> 00:22:55,070
This is bad. I'm at a disadvantage
if the fight drags on.

211
00:22:55,609 --> 00:22:58,339
And if he noticed that, then...

212
00:22:59,179 --> 00:23:02,979
Next time: "360 Degrees of Vision:
The Byakugan's Blind Spot!"
